<paragraph pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<bibRefCitation author="Bourguignat, JR" journalOrPublisher="Annales de Malacologie" pageId="303" pageNumber="304" pagination="1 - 168" publicationUrl="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/55067page/9/mode/1up" refId="B48" refString="Bourguignat, JR, 1884. Histoire des melaniens du systeme europeen. Annales de Malacologie 2: 1 - 168, http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/55067page/9/mode/1up" title="Histoire des melaniens du systeme europeen." url="http://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/55067page/9/mode/1up" volume="2" year="1884">Bourguignat (1884)</bibRefCitation>
denoted the authority as &quot;Letourneux, 1882&quot;, but there is no evidence that the description really derived from that author. 
<bibRefCitation author="Heller, J" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Conchology" pageId="313" pageNumber="314" pagination="589 - 606" refId="B227" refString="Heller, J, Sivan, N, Ben-Ami, F, 2002. Systematics of Melanopsis from the coastal plain of Israel (Gastropoda: Cerithioidea). Journal of Conchology 37 (6): 589 - 606" title="Systematics of Melanopsis from the coastal plain of Israel (Gastropoda: Cerithioidea)." volume="37" year="2002">Heller et al. (2002</bibRefCitation>
: 596) considered the species as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ludwig" authorityYear="1865" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis costata" order="Pteropoda" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="costata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Melanopsis costata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Olivier, 1804). 
<bibRefCitation author="Heller, J" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="313" pageNumber="314" pagination="229 - 260" publicationUrl="10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00172.x" refId="B222" refString="Heller, J, Mordan, P, Ben-Ami, F, Sivan, N, 2005. Conchometrics, systematics and distribution of Melanopsis (Mollusca: Gastropoda) in the Levant. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society 144: 229 - 260, DOI: 10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00172.x" title="Conchometrics, systematics and distribution of Melanopsis (Mollusca: Gastropoda) in the Levant." url="10.1111/j.1096-3642.2005.00172.x" volume="144" year="2005">Heller et al. (2005</bibRefCitation>
: 244) in turn treated it as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bourguignat" authorityYear="1884" class="Gastropoda" family="Melanopsidae" genus="Melanopsis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Melanopsis lampra" order="Pteropoda" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="lampra">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Melanopsis lampra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bourguignat, 1884.
</paragraph>
